 Northern Wei dynasty (386–534  AD ). (iii) traced back to other minority ethnic groups in ancient northwestern China.","Mandarin form of the Chinese surname 邸, meaning ‘official residence’ in Chinese: (i) from placename Di (邸), the name of a county (unidentified location). (ii) said to be borne by some descendants of Kujula Kadphises (called 丘就郤 or 邸就郤 in Chinese, 30–<i>c.</i> 80  AD ), founder of the Kushan Empire (one branch of the Yuezhi people originating from western China) located in Central Asia during the Eastern Han dynasty (25–220  AD )."],"variants":[{"name":"Chi","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Chinese Young, Dong, Yun, Cheng, Jae, Yong, Cheng Chung, Chi, Chun, Duk, Fang, Feng.  Korean Chung, Chong, Jae Hong, Moon, Myong, Pong, Shen, Yoo, Byung, Chang, Chol, Chong Hun.  Southeast Asian Phi, Hung, Ly, Tu, Denh, Do Van, Duong, Hao, Kieu, Mui, Nga, Phat.","Chinese: Mandarin and Cantonese form of the surname 池, meaning ‘moat’ in ancient Chinese: (i) acquired as a surname by people who lived beside a moat. (ii) from Chi (池), said to be the name of an ancient state (of unknown location and period). (iii) from the personal name Chi (池), personal name of a son of an official in the state of Qin during the Spring and Autumn period (770–476  BC ).","Chinese: Mandarin and Cantonese form of the surname 遲, meaning ‘late’ in Chinese: (i) borne by descendants of Chi Ren (遲任), a person who lived during the Shang dynasty (1600–1046  BC ). (ii) shortened form of the Chinese compound surname Yu-Chi (尉遲), originally the name of a tribe from the Xianbei ethnic group in northern China. (iii) from the second element of the personal name Zi Chi (子遲), style name of Fan Xu, a student of Confucius (551–479  BC )."]}]},{"name":"Curte","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Italian Amerigo, Angelo, Cesare, Ciro, Dario, Evo, Fernando, Josafat, Mario, Olivio, Ruben.","Italian: patronymic or plural form of   Curto  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Curto","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Italian Angelo, Salvatore, Sal, Fausto, Giovanni, Carmelo, Carmine, Concetta, Dino, Gioacchino, Marcello, Michelangelo.","Italian (southern), Spanish, and Portuguese: nickname for a short man, from southern Italian <i>curtu</i>, <i>curto</i>, Spanish and Portuguese <i>curto</i> ‘short’ (from Latin <i>curtus</i> ‘curtailed, truncated, cut short; broken off’).","Catalan (<b>Curtó</b>): from a diminutive of   Curt  ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Calcerana di Curte was born in Italy as the daughter of Lamberto di Curte and Mrs Lamberto di CURTE. She married Alberto di Massa. They were the parents of at least 2 sons. She died about 1150."},"et":{"–aproximadamente 1150":"–umbes 1150","–1150":"–1150","1090–1155":"1090–1155","–1202":"–1202","1040–Male":"1040–Surnud","1040–Female":"1040–Surnud","1090":"1090","aproximadamente 1150":"umbes 1150","1202":"1202","1155":"1155","aproximadamente 1090":"umbes 1090","1040":"1040","1150":"1150","Itália":"Itaalia"},"fi":{"–aproximadamente 1150":"–noin 1150","–1150":"–1150","1090–1155":"1090–1155","–1202":"–1202","1040–Male":"1040–Kuollut","1040–Female":"1040–Kuollut","1090":"1090","aproximadamente 1150":"noin 1150","1202":"1202","1155":"1155","aproximadamente 1090":"noin 1090","1040":"1040","1150":"1150","Itália":"Italia"},"fr":{"–aproximadamente 1150":"–environ 1150","–1150":"–1150","1090–1155":"1090–1155","–1202":"–1202","1040–Male":"1040–Décédé","1040–Female":"1040–Décédée","1090":"1090","aproximadamente 1150":"environ 1150","1202":"1202","1155":"1155","aproximadamente 1090":"environ 1090","1040":"1040","1150":"1150","Itália":"Italie","lifeSummary":"Calcerana di Curte est née à Italie, fille de Lamberto di Curte et Mrs Lamberto di CURTE. Elle a épousé Alberto di Massa. Ils ont eu au moins 2 fils. Elle est décédée environ 1150."},"de":{"–aproximadamente 1150":"–um 1150","–1150":"–1150","1090–1155":"1090–1155","–1202":"–1202"